Class SortedList

java.lang.Object
SortedList
public class SortedList
extends java.lang.Object
A SortedList is a linked list of double values
Version:
March 2020
Author:
Joshua Carney

    SortedList()

    • find

      public int find​(double value)
      Returns the position of "value" in the list from 0 to size - 1. If the value cannot be found, return -1.
      Parameters:
      value - the double value to search for
      Returns:
      - an integer representing the index of the given value

    • removeAt

      public boolean removeAt​(int index)
      Removes the value at the passed index
      Parameters:
      index - an int representing which 0 based index to remove
      Returns:
      true if the value was successfully removed from the list. false if the index was either less than 0 or greater than or equal to size
